Description text: Invincible class Flightdeck.  Has space for 21 aircraft.  prior to the Falklands war this was just Sea king HAS.5 ASW helos and Sea harrier FRS.Mk.1 aircraft.  Typically 9 Sea King and 5 Sea Harriers.  During the Falklands war she was filled to capacity with  Sea harrier FRS.Mk.1 and Harrier GR.Mk.3 of the RAF.  The original intended role of the Invincible class was simple that of ASW, a role best served by helos at the time.  The Falklands war proved a need for the capacity to present before the enemy with air power.  This lesson was taken to heart and the typical air group of the Invincible class after the Falklands war became 3 Sea King AEW helos, 9 Sea King ASW helos, and 8 or 9 Sea harriers.
